values:
I sit gladly for tea, and eat, and drink. He speaks to me calmly, and I listen, rarely loosing sight of his horns and tail, even as he becomes now old, now young, a woman, a man. I am polite, neither refusing nor indulging, but my ettiquette is not flawless. Sometimes he fools me into sipping a bit too deeply, or taking an extra cake.


I know he has been spit on, cursed, reviled, but he has been a kind teacher to me. I have much difficulty with him, his lessons being hard to learn, but I have grown to love him as I love his other half.
